Class: Task
This class represents one task.
It must contain:
id (int)
title (String)
description (String)
completed (boolean)
Methods:
Constructor
Getters + setters
markAsCompleted()
toString() → should print task information nicely

Class: TaskManager
This class manages all tasks.
It must contain:
ArrayList<Task> tasks
int nextId = 1 (to auto-increment task IDs)

addTask(title, description) Create new Task and add to list
removeTask(id) Remove task with that ID
updateTask(id, newTitle, newDescription) Update fields
markCompleted(id) Mark task as completed
search(keyword) Show tasks containing keyword
getAllTasks() Print all tasks
clearAll() Remove all tasks
findById(id) Return the matching Task object

====== TASK MANAGER ======
1. Add task
2. Remove task
3. Update task
4. Mark task as completed
5. Show all tasks
6. Search tasks
7. Clear all tasks
8. Exit
Choose option:


1 → Add
Ask:
Enter title:
Enter description:

2 → Remove
Ask:
Enter task ID:

3 → Update
Ask:
Enter ID:
Enter new title:
Enter new description:

4 → Mark Completed
Ask:
Enter ID:

5 → Show All
Print all tasks.
If none → print "No tasks available."

6 → Search
Ask:
Enter keyword:

7 → Clear All
Ask:
Are you sure? (yes/no)

8 → Exit
Stop the program.
